def: To work hard; to strive; to fuse. [Local]

A species of the genus Myrtus, especially Myrtus communis. Thecommon myrtle has a shrubby, upright stem, eight or ten feet high.Its branches form a close, full head, thickly covered with ovate orlanceolate evergreen leaves. It has solitary axillary white or rosyflowers, followed by black several-seeded berries. The ancientsconsidered it sacred to Venus. The flowers, leaves, and berries areused variously in perfumery and as a condiment, and the beautifullymottled wood is used in turning.
To make, or tend to make (the motion of a moving body), uniformin rate of rotation, or in frequency of vibration.

The European green woodpecker (Picus, or Genius, viridis). Itis noted for its loud laughlike note. Called also eccle, hewhole,highhoe, laughing bird, popinjay, rain bird, yaffil, yaffler,yaffingale, yappingale, yackel, and woodhack.
A dark resinous substance, polymeric with indol, and obtainedby the reduction of indigo white.
Having the form of the human ear; ear-shaped.
